      "acceptanceCriteria": "Level 3 requires that the constitutive model choice and contact formulation are justified by prior published validation studies for geometrically and materially similar problems, and that sensitivity of QoIs to model form assumptions is quantified.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity was selected based on prior titanium alloy validation studies in the orthopaedic implant literature. Frictionless vs. frictional contact sensitivity analysis showed <3% change in yield force, confirming model form robustness. Literature precedent for this formulation in ASTM F1717 simulation is well established."
